<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">
  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFrameworks>netstandard2.0;net45;net461</TargetFrameworks>
    <GenerateAssemblyInfo>true</GenerateAssemblyInfo>
    <GeneratePackageOnBuild>false</GeneratePackageOnBuild>
    <PackageId>Pipelines.Net</PackageId>
    <Authors>Sergey Solomentsev</Authors>
    <Company>Witty Lion</Company>
    <Description>Library that exposes SOLID principles by introducing pipelines.</Description>
    <Copyright>Witty Lion © 2020</Copyright>
    <PackageLicenseExpression>Apache-2.0</PackageLicenseExpression>
    <PackageProjectUrl>https://wittylion.github.io/</PackageProjectUrl>
    <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/wittylion/Pipelines.Net</RepositoryUrl>
    <RepositoryType>git</RepositoryType>
    <PackageReleaseNotes>
      A moment of happiness:
      OMG, version 1.1.7 has been downloaded more than 1000 times :)
      I am so happy, that you guys like this package. Cheers!

      New in this version:

      Added ability to modify an existing pipeline. In scope of this functionality: 
        - Added Modify extension method to pipelines;
        - Added a class called ModifiedPipeline, that accepts modifiers and a pipeline and returns processors of the original pipeline with applied to them modificators;
        - Added class ChainingModification that allows composing several different modification configurations;
        - Modification.Configure() - is an easy way to create ChainingModification;
        - IProcessorMatcher and implementations - is a functionality that helps choosing the right processor for modification.

      More information of pipeline modification can be found in this article: https://wittylion.github.io/2020/08/05/modify-pipeline.html

      Also check out new Pipelines.Net.Xml library: https://www.nuget.org/packages/Pipelines.Net.Xml/
      More information on using Pipelines.Net.Xml library you can find here: https://wittylion.github.io/2019/11/22/pipelines-net-xml.html

      Please take the survey:
      https://forms.gle/Y8aogzwPQ3sLKXMCA
      This inspires and helps wittylion get better.

    </PackageReleaseNotes>
    <NeutralLanguage>English</NeutralLanguage>
    <PackageTags>Pipelines SOLID Processors Chain</PackageTags>
    <Version>1.1.8</Version>
    <AssemblyVersion>1.1.8.0</AssemblyVersion>
    <PackageIcon>pipelines-icon.png</PackageIcon>
    <PublishRepositoryUrl>true</PublishRepositoryUrl>
    <EmbedUntrackedSources>true</EmbedUntrackedSources>
    <IncludeSymbols>true</IncludeSymbols>
    <SymbolPackageFormat>snupkg</SymbolPackageFormat>
  </PropertyGroup>
  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.SourceLink.GitHub" Version="1.0.0" PrivateAssets="All"/>
    <None Include="pipelines-icon.png" Pack="true" Visible="false" PackagePath="" />
  </ItemGroup>
</Project>
